{"id": "12133", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12133", "title": "Armour Piercing Grenade", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;grenade&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a throwable grenade that deals Piercing Damage in 4 meter radius. \nAll characters can throw this grenade. However due to its damage type it is not possible to increase its damage output directly through abilities. The only possible bonuses may come from &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; ability which increases damage bonus through height difference and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; ability which allows the caster (&lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; included) to heal themselves through damage done to Vitality. Since Piercing Damage always bypasses all armour characters with \"Necromancer ability\" will always heal themselves through damage done this way.\nSince is a grenade it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent which decreases the cost of using grenades and scrolls by 1 AP when the secondary hand is free. is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; which increases its range by 5 meters and by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent which increases range by 2 meters."}
{"id": "5550", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5550", "title": "Armour Specialist", "text": "The armour specialist ability increases a character's armour rating by a percent amount, and reduces the movement penalty from wearing armour. Maximum level armour specialist would allow one to move unrestricted even when wearing heavy plate-mail."}
{"id": "10154", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10154", "title": "Armour Specialist (DOS EE)", "text": "General.\nThe Armour Specialist skill is generally used by characters, as they benefit the most from having their movement speed less affected by wearing their heavy &lt;a href=\"Armour%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;. It also reduces movement speed penalties from using crossbows. Any class could invest in this purely for the defensive bonus."}
{"id": "11385", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11385", "title": "Armour of Frost (Original Sin 2)", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive hydrosophist skill that allows character to conjure an icy defensive barrier around their target, which provides &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Shell%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Magic Shell&lt;/a&gt; status effect that restores Magic Armour each turn for 3 turns but also increases the maximum amount of it. Alongside these effects the will also remove &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stunned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Stunned&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Suffocating%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Suffocating&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Petrified%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Petrified&lt;/a&gt; status effects. Since this skill applies positive status effect it will always bypass armour. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophy\"&gt;Hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Water%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Water Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a starter Hydrosophist skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Hydrosophist skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 60 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive skill whose effects depend on the following characteristics of the caster:\nOutside of the Level of the caster only their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; ability can influence the amount of Magic Armour gained by . \n properties can be affected by talents and other skills only. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell hydrosophist spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met. Also note that &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Dreamer\"&gt;Lizard Dreamer&lt;/a&gt; requires a persuasion check to be passed in order to speak with him, otherwise he (and the whole encampment) will turn hostile. "}
