{"id": "18574", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18574", "title": "Attributes (Original Sin)", "text": ""}
{"id": "19967", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19967", "title": "Attributes and Abilities (Original Sin)", "text": "This page provides a summary list of all attributes and abilities in ' and '.\nDivinity: Original Sin.\nAttributes.\nAttributes are a character's basic stats that affect their health, offense and defense, weight capacity, sight, skill effectiveness, etc. These are assigned at character creation and grow as the character levels, along with (&lt;a href=\"Talents%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;EE&lt;/a&gt;) and &lt;a href=\"Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Abilities&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=\"Abilities%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;EE&lt;/a&gt;).\nInitial Assignment and Growth.\nAll Attributes start at base 5. A newly created character has five Attribute points to spend. Each even level grants an additional Attribute point, ending up with 15 spendable Attribute Points. Attributes cannot exceed 15 unless it is boosted by equipment.\nEffect on Skills.\nEach &lt;a href=\"Skills%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; is boosted by a particular Attribute and has a &lt;a href=\"Skills%20%28Original%20Sin%29%23Minimum%20Attribute%20Effectiveness\"&gt;soft Attribute requirement&lt;/a&gt; based on its Skill Level. Each Attribute point below the requirement reduces the effectiveness of the Skill by 10%, while each Attribute point above the requirement grants a 5% bonus.\nAbilities.\nAbilities are divided into 6 branches that offer different bonuses. While some abilities offer gains only up to level 5, some benefit from 6 or more points.\nDivinity: Original Sin Enhanced Edition.\nAbilities.\nLeveling up an ability costs ability points equal to the new level. For example, leveling Leadership from 2 to 3 costs 3 points. The cost of leveling an ability is not affected by bonuses gained from Gear or Traits giving significant reduction in the cost of maxing out abilities."}
