{"id": "5052", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5052", "title": "Battering Ram", "text": "Battering Ram is a &lt;a href=\"Warfare%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Warfare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive warfare skill that allows caster to dash forward in a straight line and hit all enemies in path with their melee weapon.\nCharacters without Physical Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Knocked%20Down%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Knocked Down&lt;/a&gt; status effect which will make them incapable to act their next turn.\nSince requires a weapon it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Atrophy%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Atrophy&lt;/a&gt; status effect.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. Since is a starter Warfare skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Warfare skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well.\nSince is a weapon based skill and as such it does not have a scroll. It is also not possible to craft a skillbook.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus %) x (1 + Attribute Bonus % + Weapon Skill Bonus % + Misc Bonuses % ) x (1 + High Ground Bonus % + Crit Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Compatible attribute provides the lowest bonus out of the three (example: 3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Pyrokinetic).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills.\nLocations.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell warfare skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Gareth\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if his demands are met."}
