{"id": "3556", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3556", "title": "Battle Rage", "text": "Battle Rage is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Warrior\"&gt;Warrior skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nBattle Rage is a active Warrior skill that allows the Knight to greatly boost their damage at the cost of their armour. This skill can be cast with any weapon in hand. \nNote: This skill will never drop your melee resistance below 0%.\u00a0Melee armor penalty values are not subtracted directly to damage reduction.\u00a0A higher armor value on your character sheet will yield a smaller penalty to your overall melee armor. For example, with 57.56% unbuffed melee resistance the -33 armor penalty reduces the character to 47.33% melee damage reduction; this is a reduction of 10.23%.\u00a0With 37.35% unbuffed melee resistance the -33 armor penalty reduces the player to\u00a012.18%; a reduction of 25.17%.\nBattle Rage be canceled at any time, the cooldown starts after the duration ends or after Battle Rage is manually turned off.\nThe following are mutually exclusive, only one can be active: &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Battle%20Mage\"&gt;Way of the Battle Mage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Wise%20Wizard\"&gt;Way of the Wise Wizard&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Ranger\"&gt;Way of the Ranger&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Rage\"&gt;Battle Rage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Posture\"&gt;Defensive Posture&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "10372", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10372", "title": "Battle Stomp", "text": "Battle Stomp is a &lt;a href=\"Warfare%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Warfare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive warfare skill that allows caster to smash their melee weapon into the ground in front of them. This will send off a shockwave that will deal damage to all non-allied characters and clear all not cursed surfaces and clouds with the exception of lava and deathfog.\nCharacters without Physical Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Knocked%20Down%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Knocked Down&lt;/a&gt; status effect which will make them incapable to act their next turn.\nSince requires a weapon it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Atrophy%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Atrophy&lt;/a&gt; status effect. \nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. Since is a starter Warfare skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Warfare skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well.\nSince is a weapon based skill and as such it does not have a scroll. It is also not possible to craft a skillbook.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus %) x (1 + Attribute Bonus % + Weapon Skill Bonus % + Misc Bonuses % ) x (1 + High Ground Bonus % + Crit Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Compatible attribute provides the lowest bonus out of the three (example: 3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Pyrokinetic).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell warfare skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Gareth\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if his demands are met."}
{"id": "2216", "revid": "47788234", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2216", "title": "Battle Tower", "text": "The Battle Tower is a location on &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island\"&gt;Sentinel Island&lt;/a&gt; in \". Many outstanding quests in &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt; will be failed after assuming control of the tower as it is not possible to return to the &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley%20Village\"&gt;village&lt;/a&gt; or surface of the valley.\nBackground.\nOnce ruled by the great magician, &lt;a href=\"Maxos\"&gt;Maxos&lt;/a&gt; before he disappeared, it was commandeered by the evil necromancer, &lt;a href=\"Laiken\"&gt;Laiken&lt;/a&gt; years later.\nThe necromancer broke the magical wards on it and took it over using it for his evil experiments on the undead until &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; arrived in 1300 AD and assumed control.\nPlatforms.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;Skill Trainers&lt;/a&gt; within these areas depend on the Knight's choices during &lt;a href=\"The%20Prophecy%20%28quest%29\"&gt;The Prophecy&lt;/a&gt;."}
