{"id": "3142", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3142", "title": "Beyond Divinity", "text": "Beyond Divinity is the second game in the \"Divinity\" &lt;a href=\"series\"&gt;series&lt;/a&gt; which followed up on \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThe Story So Far.\nYou are a servant of &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;the Divine&lt;/a&gt; - scourge of necromancers and sorcerers alike. Your purpose in life is to fight all that is evil using any means possible. Your dilemma\u2026 during an intense battle with one of the great necromancers, a &lt;a href=\"Demons\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; drags you into its universe. There you are soul-forged with a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Knight\"&gt;Death-knight&lt;/a&gt;. You are cursed and destined to spend the rest of eternity bonded to this creature of evil.\nOr maybe not...\nThe Death-knight dislikes the soul forging as much as you do and together you embark on a great adventure. You both have a common goal - to undo the soul forging. You and your unlikely companion quickly figure out that the only way to rid this curse is if you unlock the secret of riftrunning \u2013 an ancient art that allowed the prison universe\u2019s indigenous &lt;a href=\"Raanaar\"&gt;population&lt;/a&gt; to travel between universes.\nYour quest is set: To become a Riftrunner! \nPlot.\nSet in the realm of &lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt; in 1238 AD, &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Damian&lt;/a&gt;, under the guise of a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Knight\"&gt;Death Knight&lt;/a&gt;, is soul forged to a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; who fell through a rift created by the demon &lt;a href=\"Samuel\"&gt;Samuel&lt;/a&gt;. The two are forced to work together to escape Nemesis.\nSee Also.\nGuides.\nFollowing list shows generic guides and summary pages associated with \"Beyond Divinity\". For more specific guides for this game refer to: &lt;a href=\"Beyond%20Divinity%20Guides\"&gt;Beyond Divinity Guides&lt;/a&gt;."}
