{"id": "10684", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10684", "title": "Birdie", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"source%20hound\"&gt;source hound&lt;/a&gt; in 1242 AD.\nBackground.\nBirdie, a hound subjected to mistreatment and fed tainted meat in an attempt to transform him into a source hound, resides within &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy%20Prison\"&gt;Fort Joy Prison&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found in the Houndmaster's bedroom, connected to the Houndmaster's Room, at (X:333 Y:666).\nInteractions.\nBirdie laments the irreparable corruption of his mind due to his indoctrination training and expresses a desire for peace. The &lt;a href=\"Elaborate%20Cage%20Key\"&gt;Elaborate Cage Key&lt;/a&gt;, which unlocks his cage, can be found on a desk near the bed in the same room.\nFreeing Birdie from his cage rewards you with 1000 XP. Birdie will attack unless a character possesses the Pet Pal talent. The following checks may successfully persuade Birdie:\nIf persuasion is successfull, Birdie will leave as a free dog. Alternatively, the player may agree to put Birdie down at the dog's request. Successfully persuading Birdie from turning (or killing him at his request) grants 1400 XP."}
