{"id": "18454", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18454", "title": "Biscoe", "text": " is one of the two remaining &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis%20Characters\"&gt;guards&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island%20Encampment\"&gt;encampment&lt;/a&gt; of the shipwrecked \"Starbound\" on &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island\"&gt;Sentinel Island&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nPresumably a crewmate of the \"Starbound\", Biscoe was marooned alongside the rest of the crew when the ship was magically transported to &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island\"&gt;Sentinel Island&lt;/a&gt;. He and &lt;a href=\"Pedro%20%28Sentinel%20Island%29\"&gt;Pedro&lt;/a&gt; guard the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island%20Encampment\"&gt;encampment&lt;/a&gt; established around the \"Starbound\"'s wreck, defending it from the various creatures that roam the island.\nWhen the Dragon Knight approaches, Biscoe and Pedro can be seen discussing the attacks on the camp. Biscoe expresses his confidence in their ability to repel future attacks despite losing 3 men during the last attack, stating that he likes \"to think of the keg o' rum as half full\".\nWhat becomes of him and the rest of the \"Starbound\"'s crew after Sentinel Island is shrouded in Deathfog is unknown, though it is unlikely he survived."}
