{"id": "16108", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16108", "title": "Blayre Cydow", "text": "Blayer Cydow is a human spirit haunting the archives on &lt;a href=\"Bloodmoon%20Island\"&gt;Bloodmoon Island&lt;/a&gt; in 1242 AD.\nBackground.\nAn archivist on the Bloodmoon island. She took care of the archive when &lt;a href=\"doctor%20Daeva\"&gt;doctor Daeva&lt;/a&gt; brought &lt;a href=\"Eleanalessa\"&gt;Eleanalessa&lt;/a&gt; to the island and unleashed the demon. How she died is not certain, however her spirit continues to search the archives for the missing hymnals."}
{"id": "3613", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3613", "title": "Bleed", "text": "Bleed is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Warrior\"&gt;Warrior skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nBleed is a passive Warrior skill that gives the Knight a chance to cause bleeding with their attacks. This skill can be cast only with melee weapon in hand or free hands. Due to its nature, once learnt, it will be always active. Note that the damage of the bleed debuff is based on the hit that \"bled\" the enemy and the amount of damage listed is done per second.\u00a0E.g. A hit for 100 damage with Level 1 Bleed would do 100% of the total melee damage (100 damage total) over 10 seconds."}
{"id": "10506", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10506", "title": "Bleed Fire", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; skill in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive mixed skill that allows caster to curse target characters (without Magic Armour) in 3 meter radius to bleed fire, while lowering their Fire Resistance by 20 %. Alongside the curse, this skill conjures a a blood surface in 4 meter radius of the target which is immediately ignited and turned into fire surface. Characters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt; status due to the fire surface and suffer damage directly to their health. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;Pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Metamorphosis\"&gt;Metamorphosis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into both &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a any non-source &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks are combined. Since is a mixed skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a offensive skill that in itself deals no damage, however it will make target take indirect damage through the creation of fire surfaces. Note that the Fire Resistance debuff stacks with other Fire Resistance debuffs.\nThe only way to improve this skill is to increase its range through skills or talents.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from NPCs in the game."}
{"id": "20262", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20262", "title": "Bleeding (Status)", "text": "Bleeding is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nBleeding is a negative status effect. Characters afflicted by it will receive X-Y piercing damage each turn. Piercing damage deals damage directly to Vitality and is not affected by Armour values. \nCause.\nBleeding can be caused by both items and skills. On &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; there is no surface which will inflict bleeding status. On the other hand &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; schools have access to skills and spells which will inflict Bleeding. \nTreatment.\nAs with any other negative status effect, there are two ways how to avoid and negate its effects. First its important to keep Physical armour value above 0. Secondly status effect &lt;a href=\"Regenerating%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Regenerating&lt;/a&gt; protect from being affected by Bleeding and also replaces the effect. Regenerating can be gained by both spells and \"blessed poison surface\" or \"blessed poison cloud\".\nPhysical armour restoration.\nBleeding can be resisted if character has Physical armour above 0. This does not apply to characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Glass Cannon&lt;/a&gt; talent.\nStatus removal.\nFollowing items and spells/skills will remove Bleeding status entirely."}
