{"id": "20259", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20259", "title": "Blinded (Status)", "text": "Blinded is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nBlinded is a negative status effect that appliable to characters. Blinded characters will suffer penalty to their accuracy - 35 % and will be unable to perform &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;attacks of opportunity&lt;/a&gt;. Alongside this their range will be greatly reduced.\nCause.\nBlinded can be caused either by \"cursed smoke cloud\" or by spells. \nNote that all of these spells will inflict Blind status if target does not have Magic Armour.\nTreatment.\nBlinded is a negative status effect, as such it is resisted by Magic armour. Certain spells will also cancel out the status effect as well as &lt;a href=\"Rested%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Rested status&lt;/a&gt;.\nMagic armour restoration.\nCursed can be resisted if character has Magic armour above. This does not apply to characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Glass Cannon&lt;/a&gt; talent.\nFollowing spells will remove Blinded status entirely."}
{"id": "11374", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11374", "title": "Blinding Radiance (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Blinding Radiance is a &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive aerotheurge skill that allows caster to unleash an aura of bright light around themselves in 5 meter radius. The aura will deal air damage upon being unleashed. \nCharacters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Blinded%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Blinded&lt;/a&gt; status effect if they are in 5 meter range from the caster when they are affected by the Radiant status effect for 1 turn. The &lt;a href=\"Blinded%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Blinded&lt;/a&gt; status effect will immediately wear off once enemy character is further than 5 meters from the caster.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurgy\"&gt;Aerotheurgy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is not reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Air%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Air Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a starter Aerotheurge skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Aerotheurge skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 60 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Aerotheurge ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Aerotheurge).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist air damage if they have: Air Immunity Status and high enough Air Resistance (which lowers air damage done).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell hydrosophist spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met. Also note that &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Dreamer\"&gt;Lizard Dreamer&lt;/a&gt; requires a persuasion check to be passed in order to speak with him, otherwise he (and the whole encampment) will turn hostile. "}
