{"id": "20095", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20095", "title": "Blood Infusion", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive mixed skill that allows caster to change their summoned Incarnate's element to blood. By changing the element, the Incarnate gains multiple boons associated with it. Its basic close attack will deal physical damage. Due to the Incarnate being infused with blood it gains increased Maximum Magic Armour and Maximum Physical Armour by + 15 % each.\nBesides Magic and Physical Armour being increased the Incarnate becomes immune to &lt;a href=\"Bleeding%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Bleeding&lt;/a&gt; status effect. Alongside this the Incarnate learns the Necromancer skill &lt;a href=\"Mosquito%20Swarm\"&gt;Mosquito Swarm&lt;/a&gt;. Lastly it will receive + 5 points to &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; and + 1 point to &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; abilities.\nThe effects of are achieved by summoning the Incarnate unto any blood surface. Note that this skill is part of the feature Pet Power and it is not present in the game as a craftable/usable skill unless the feature has been manually activated.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Necromancy\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from NPCs in the game.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift Bag: Pet Power allows this skill to be used on any summoned creature. This gift bag also shortens the cooldown of this skill from 3 turns to 1 turn. Following table shows what skills will specific summoned entity gain from . Note that there are no changes to the skill and bonuses granted by the skill to the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;."}
