{"id": "16076", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16076", "title": "Blood Storm", "text": "Blood storm is a &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; source skill in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nBolts of coagulated blood fall on enemy characters in the area dealing physical damage and setting &lt;a href=\"Diseased%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Diseased&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Decaying%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Decaying&lt;/a&gt;. Turns water in the area into blood.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into both &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted by combining any &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks out of which atleast one must be a source skillbook. Since is a mixed source skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nLocation.\nTraders.\nThis source skill cannot be bought or stolen from any NPCs in the game."}
{"id": "10407", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10407", "title": "Blood Sucker", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive necromancer skill that allows caster to heal themselves, their ally or neutral character up to 13 meters from them, if there is a blood surface and blood clouds (both of any type) up to 3 meters from them. The amount of blood surface in reach of the chosen target character indicates how much of indicated Vitality will be restored when the surface is absorbed. Note that the skill heals a set amount of Vitality and not a certain percentage of Vitality. Following table shows how much health is restored if certain amount of blood surface or cloud is in the reach of a target character. Note that if both surface and cloud are present they will be both absorped and the amount of health restored will be increased as well. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Necromancy\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. Alongside this due to its reliance on Necromancy it will also restore Vitality of the &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;. However it will deal physical damage if target is afflicted by &lt;a href=\"Decaying%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Decaying&lt;/a&gt; status effect.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Necromancy%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Necromancy Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a starter Necromancer skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Necromancer skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 60 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive skill whose effects depend on the following characteristics of the caster:\nOut of these, Level provides the greatest boon. In case of healing itself the main factor is how many points caster has in &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; ability, however this also affects how much physical damage this skill deals to the Undead. Note that, since the skill causes physical damage to the Undead it is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; ability whose bonus stacks with that of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt;.\n properties can be affected by talents and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell necromancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only \"&lt;a href=\"Tarquin\"&gt;Tarquin&lt;/a&gt;\" is guaranteed to follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; as they travel with &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;. \"&lt;a href=\"Jahan\"&gt;Jahan&lt;/a&gt;\" may join the Godwoken on the ship as well if his demands are met. "}
