{"id": "15052", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15052", "title": "Boar", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20creatures\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiology.\nBoars are muscular mammals with tusks which they use to impale threats if provoked.\nCharacteristics.\nThey are hostile to &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt;. A boar attacks by running towards its target and hitting it with its tusks. Boars drop &lt;a href=\"Meat\"&gt;meat&lt;/a&gt; when killed. They are found in forests, commonly in the elevated areas at eastern part of &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt;, around the Dwarven Forest.\nImmune to spiritual damage.\nTransformed Boar.\nThere is a talking boar encountered in &lt;a href=\"Teneb%20Tiriel\"&gt;Teneb Tiriel&lt;/a&gt;, which tells Lucian about an &lt;a href=\"Evil%20Transformation\"&gt;Evil Transformation&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "10155", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10155", "title": "Body Building (DOS EE)", "text": "General.\nThe Body Building skill reduces the chance of being &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;Knocked Down, Burned, Frozen, Bleeding, Crippled, Blinded, Weakened, Diseased, Infected, and Drunk&lt;/a&gt;. This is very important for melee characters, as they are the most likely to be the target of crowd control.\nScaling.\nFor a skill / spell that has a Bodybuilding defense, Bodybuilding affects the success chance of any harmful effect the skill applies. Other values, like damage, are not affected. More specifically, if BB is the Bodybuilding of the spell target, the success chance of the effect is multiplied by:\n1 \u2013 0.15 * BB (or 100% - 15% * BB). Here is an example:\nLet's say a wizard with INT 12 is trying to freeze an enemy fighter using the Freezing Touch spell. This spell has a 100% base success chance and INT will raise it to 120% (see the &lt;a href=\"Skills%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;skills page&lt;/a&gt;).\nOn the other side, let's say the fighter's Bodybuilding is 2. This means that the success ratio of the effect is limited by a 1 \u2013 0.15 * 2 = 0.7 factor.\nThe overall success chance of the Freezing Touch spell is the product of the two figures above, which is 120% x 0.7 = 84%. So the fighter finally has a 100 - 84 = 16% chance to avoid freezing. This last figure is reported in the statistics window at the bottom right corner of the screen (maybe +/- 1 because of rounding)."}
{"id": "14237", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14237", "title": "Boiled Potato", "text": "The boiled potato is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Consumables\"&gt;consumable item&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a consumable item which will heal 10 % of maximum Vitality and grant + 1 point to &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; upon consuming. If character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; it will heal 20 % of maximum Vitality and grant + 2 points to Constitution. The effect of last 6 turns.\nPoisoned is a consumable item that was poisoned through various means (either &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Bottle%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;poison bottle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Zaikk%27s%20Talon\"&gt;Zaikk's Talon&lt;/a&gt;). Poisoning the will reduce its value to 0. Instead of healing it will deal poison damage equal to 10 % of the consumers maximum Vitality, rendering it unsafe for the living but safe for &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; and grant + 2 points to &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt;. \nIf character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; the will deal poison damage equal to 20 % of the consumers maximum Vitality and grant + 2 points to Constitution. The effects last 6 turns. \nNote that poisoned item may be used in crafting, however the end product will be un-poisoned item.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for. "}
